longBusinessSummary: Tsim Sha Tsui Properties Limited, an investment holding company, invests in, develops, manages, and trades in properties primarily in the Hong Kong, Mainland China, Singapore, and Australia. It operates through six segments: Property Sales; Property Rental; Property Management and Other Services; Hotel Operations; Investments in Securities; and Financing. The company is also involved in the securities investment and dealing, mortgage loan financing, building construction and management, and project management activities. In addition, it offers cleaning, management, premium living, secretarial, consultancy, administrative, deposit placing, financing, and security services. The company's property portfolio includes residential, commercial, industrial, hotels and car parks. As of June 30, 2022, it had a land bank of approximately 20.4 million square feet floor area. The company was incorporated in 1972 and is based in Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong.
